<L>__{exterior westwood cottage morning}
<A>__{up the walkway.}
<C>__{me }
<D>__{retreat to meg's. my kid sister and only living family. mom and pop died in `51 when their first plane ride became their last.}
<A>__{scoop meg's la herald of the ground. headlines condemn me. tuck it under my arm as meg opens the door:}
<C>__{meg}
<P>__{(glances from paper to me)}
<D>__{i already got the times inside.}
<L>__{interior westwood cottage moments later}
<A>__{silver tea pot over blue flame on olive drab stove. the times open on the table between us...same shitty headlines.}
<C>__{meg}
<D>__{how much is true?}
<C>__{me}
<D>__{how many times have i lied to you?}
<C>__{meg}
<D>__{zero.}
<A>__{shrug. play aloof. hope it suffices.}
<C>__{me}
<D>__{you've always liked your men mean.}
<A>__{she looks up at me. feels the shame i shun...}
<C>__{me}
<D>__{what would mom and dad say?}
<C>__{me}
<D>__{nothing. that's where i learned it.}
<A>__{she stands, goes to the stove.}
<C>__{meg}
<D>__{poor you.}
<C>__{me}
<D>__{yeah, pour me...a cup please. black, no sugar.}
<A>__{meg stares darts. i smile to defuse.}
<C>__{me }
<D>__{pretty please.}
<A>__{she fetches cups and saucers.}
<C>__{me }
<D>__{how's work?}
<C>__{meg}
<D>__{it's work.}
<C>__{me}
<D>__{how's pete?}
<C>__{meg}
<D>__{more work.}
<A>__{quiet while we wait for the pot...and quiet always means creeping sleep: an enemy i never stop fighting. force my eyes open, shift in my seat: i've been exhausted for years. i drift despite my best efforts and for a split second you see the hell i see when sleep wins:}
